A vintage 1960s scientific laboratory scene with brass syringes and glass vials containing swirling luminescent code-like patterns in amber and deep blue, being carefully injected into an intricate mechanical clockwork device made of copper gears and vacuum tubes. The scene is lit by warm Edison bulbs casting dramatic shadows across a mahogany workbench covered in technical blueprints and aged paper scrolls. Steam wisps curl through the air as the injection transforms the mechanical heart of the device, causing it to glow with new energy. Muted sepia tones with pops of electric blue and amber, shot from a dramatic low angle emphasizing the mad-scientist atmosphere of creative technical modification.
